  "_comment": "Depth-coverage registry — source of truth for scripts/check_depth_coverage.py and docs/DEPTH_COVERAGE_MATRIX.md. Every AST op in inc/eshkol/eshkol.h MUST appear under `ops` classified as 'composable' (can nest within itself / other forms, so a depth-dependent miscompile like reverse-over-nested-forward is possible) or 'leaf' (opaque-handle primitive / declaration / predicate — no user-syntactic nesting depth). Every composable MUST either name the owning depth-sweep pillar (P6a..P6f) or carry a gap_task acknowledging it is un-swept. Adding a new op without classifying it, or a new composable with neither pillar nor gap_task, FAILS the gate.",
  "pillars": {
    "P6a": "AD depth (test/ad-depth-parametric) — derivative^n, gradient-over-nested-forward, jacobian/hessian nesting, mixed fwd/reverse",
    "P6b": "Recursion/control depth (test/recursion-depth-parametric) — self/mutual tail, non-tail, CPS chains, recursion-through-map/eval, call/cc & dynamic-wind nesting",
    "P6c": "Syntax/data nesting depth (test/nesting-depth-parametric) — nested let-family/lambda/quote-family/define scopes, nested guard/raise, nested lists/vectors, multiple-values, records",
    "P6d": "Numeric depth (test/numeric-depth-parametric) — arithmetic nesting across the numeric tower (int/bignum/rational/complex/double)",
    "P6e": "Metaprog/module depth (test/metaprog-depth-parametric) — nested macros (define/let/letrec-syntax), cond-expand, include, import/require/provide chains, define-type",
    "P6f": "Tensor/collection/string depth (test/tensor-collection-depth) — nested tensors, collection higher-order fns, string composition"
  },
  "fixed_depth_harnesses": {
    "ad_oracle": "tests/ad_oracle — fixed AD nest cells (dofd/gofd/gofg), depth <=1 reverse-outer",
